267
00:16:12,760 --> 00:16:16,600
I'm sure that's why you initially
turned down doing the show.

268
00:16:16,600 --> 00:16:20,390
Actually, I didn't think that far.

269
00:16:20,390 --> 00:16:22,370
I didn't know all of that would still remain.

270
00:16:22,370 --> 00:16:24,290
I'm sorry.

271
00:16:24,290 --> 00:16:28,350
If you're considering dropping out even now...

272
00:16:29,270 --> 00:16:31,680
I'll do better.

273
00:16:32,490 --> 00:16:34,280
No.

274
00:16:34,280 --> 00:16:38,310
I'm fine as long as the program
isn't negatively affected by me.

275
00:16:38,310 --> 00:16:42,220
I'll leave it in your hands until the end.

276
00:16:43,930 --> 00:16:45,620
Thank you.

277
00:16:45,620 --> 00:16:47,790
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

278
00:17:03,610 --> 00:17:07,830
- Hey, Nu Ri.
 - Oppa, don't you need to explain? 

279
00:17:07,830 --> 00:17:10,190
 Looks like there's a filming. 

280
00:17:11,870 --> 00:17:13,420
Where are you?

281
00:17:17,780 --> 00:17:19,260
I'll explain.

282
00:17:19,260 --> 00:17:23,200
Oppa, you've really lost it over money.

283
00:17:23,200 --> 00:17:26,110
I heard people pay to be on TV these days.

284
00:17:26,110 --> 00:17:29,060
- And you wouldn't do it if it costs you money.
- Right on.

285
00:17:29,060 --> 00:17:32,660
Why would a broadcasting station
advertise a random flower shop?

286
00:17:32,660 --> 00:17:33,750
Nope.

287
00:17:33,750 --> 00:17:35,890
- What is it, then?
- That's what I mean.

288
00:17:35,890 --> 00:17:37,130
What are you asking?

289
00:17:37,130 --> 00:17:41,070
I just wanted to criticize you.
It seemed like you were crazy for money.

290
00:17:41,070 --> 00:17:42,360
Excuse me.

291
00:17:42,360 --> 00:17:43,920
Yes.

292
00:17:43,920 --> 00:17:46,050
Here's the ice cream you ordered.

293
00:17:46,050 --> 00:17:48,730
- Thank you.
- And...

294
00:17:48,730 --> 00:17:51,070
I won't take the payment.

295
00:17:51,070 --> 00:17:53,980
You always pass out flowers.

296
00:17:56,010 --> 00:17:57,830
Thank you. I'll enjoy this.

297
00:17:57,830 --> 00:17:59,650
Thank you.

298
00:18:03,890 --> 00:18:06,620
Come on.

299
00:18:06,620 --> 00:18:09,430
My childhood story will also air.

300
00:18:09,430 --> 00:18:12,390
You didn't look like a child when you were little.

301
00:18:12,390 --> 00:18:16,620
Do you still scatter your leftover
flowers in the area?

302
00:18:16,620 --> 00:18:19,730
That'd get you in huge trouble.

303
00:18:19,730 --> 00:18:22,460
Eat it. Before it melts.

304
00:18:22,460 --> 00:18:24,010
Eat a lot.

305
00:18:25,350 --> 00:18:26,830
Is it tasty?

306
00:18:29,740 --> 00:18:33,500
I thought I'd pick up some coffee for the PD.

307
00:18:34,770 --> 00:18:36,060
Who?

308
00:18:36,060 --> 00:18:39,190
Hello. I'm his sister.

309
00:18:40,030 --> 00:18:42,090
Are you shooting with Oppa?

310
00:18:42,090 --> 00:18:45,120
You really grew a lot.

311
00:18:45,120 --> 00:18:48,960
Hello. I'm the manager
of the actress he's shooting with.

312
00:18:48,960 --> 00:18:50,740
But how do you know me?

313
00:18:50,740 --> 00:18:54,390
Did you become that close to my oppa?

314
00:18:54,390 --> 00:18:56,850
I guess you don't remember.

315
00:18:56,850 --> 00:18:59,770
I used to read to you when you were little.

316
00:18:59,770 --> 00:19:02,720
Book? Book...

317
00:19:02,720 --> 00:19:06,400
 A small stone slipped away... 

318
00:19:06,400 --> 00:19:10,060
 I like her, too. 

319
00:19:14,890 --> 00:19:18,380
Unni, fighting on your shoot.

320
00:19:18,380 --> 00:19:20,050
Share it with her.

321
00:19:20,920 --> 00:19:23,170
What's with her...

322
00:19:23,170 --> 00:19:25,490
It was great to see you again.

323
00:19:26,420 --> 00:19:29,100
She really grew a lot.

324
00:19:30,990 --> 00:19:33,970
Sounds like she didn't see it.

325
00:19:33,970 --> 00:19:35,630
That's good.

326
00:19:39,280 --> 00:19:42,200
- This was you, Oppa?
- Yeah.

327
00:19:42,200 --> 00:19:43,990
- Why? Can't it?
- What happened to you?

328
00:19:43,990 --> 00:19:46,630
What do I look like that everyone keeps saying...

329
00:19:47,840 --> 00:19:50,180
- Seriously...
 - Hello, I'm Sunwoo Hae... 

330
00:19:50,180 --> 00:19:52,490
You always seemed huge to me.

331
00:19:52,490 --> 00:19:54,770
But he's so small.

332
00:19:55,840 --> 00:19:57,380
But he's so cute.

333
00:19:57,380 --> 00:19:59,530
Aren't I cute now?

334
00:20:01,870 --> 00:20:04,360
- When will you bring me your report card?
- You're cute.

335
00:20:04,360 --> 00:20:06,430
You're the cutest in the world.

336
00:20:06,430 --> 00:20:08,520
- The cutest in the world.
- It's getting late.

337
00:20:08,520 --> 00:20:11,810
- I don't think it's late yet.
- Hey.

338
00:20:11,810 --> 00:20:15,980
That Unni from earlier. It's her. Isn't she?

339
00:20:15,980 --> 00:20:17,500
Come here.

340
00:20:17,500 --> 00:20:18,930
I'm right!

341
00:20:18,930 --> 00:20:22,150
What grade did you get that you keep hiding it?

342
00:20:22,150 --> 00:20:25,470
Hey, Eun Nu Ri. Talk to me.

343
00:21:25,450 --> 00:21:30,270
Hey, the weather is too nice
for me to just go home.

344
00:21:30,270 --> 00:21:32,480
 How come Je Yeon isn't picking up my calls? 

345
00:21:32,480 --> 00:21:34,090
How would I know?

346
00:21:34,090 --> 00:21:37,480
 I feel like she has a hobby, but 

347
00:21:37,480 --> 00:21:40,820
 she won't tell her coworkers. 

348
00:21:40,820 --> 00:21:44,620
She didn't even go hiking with me today.

349
00:21:44,620 --> 00:21:49,350
So, I have nothing to do after.

350
00:21:49,350 --> 00:21:51,270
So...

351
00:21:52,360 --> 00:21:56,940
why are you telling me all this? Are you bored?

352
00:21:56,940 --> 00:21:59,280
 Yeah. I'm off today. 

353
00:21:59,280 --> 00:22:01,180
 I can come hang out, right? 

354
00:22:01,180 --> 00:22:03,330
Oppa, you're bored, too.

355
00:22:03,330 --> 00:22:06,590
Don't you feel lonely now that
the bustle of the film crew is gone?

356
00:22:06,590 --> 00:22:09,800
 Must I see you today when
we'll meet in a few days, anyway? 

357
00:22:09,800 --> 00:22:12,670
You'll have some coffee, right?
I'll bring you some.

358
00:22:12,670 --> 00:22:16,450
I keep telling you not to come. You know?

359
00:22:17,450 --> 00:22:20,400
Hello? Hello-

360
00:22:21,670 --> 00:22:23,410
She hung up.

361
00:22:45,510 --> 00:22:48,500
- Aigoo, hello.
- Hello.

362
00:22:48,500 --> 00:22:51,650
It's our first time here.
Can we ask you for directions?

363
00:22:51,650 --> 00:22:54,060
I'm sorry, but I'm lost, too.

364
00:22:54,060 --> 00:22:57,950
Oh, my! So, you are!

365
00:22:57,950 --> 00:22:59,980
But you have such great energy.

366
00:22:59,980 --> 00:23:01,390
Oh, thank you.

367
00:23:01,390 --> 00:23:04,510
Are you in the arts?

368
00:23:04,510 --> 00:23:07,760
It looks like your ancestors
accrued lots of good karma.

369
00:23:07,760 --> 00:23:10,770
Do you know my ancestors?

370
00:23:10,770 --> 00:23:13,660
I told you not to go around alone, babe.

371
00:23:31,090 --> 00:23:35,060
So, you had a friend with you.

372
00:23:35,060 --> 00:23:38,570
He looks like a stranger. Can we help?

373
00:23:38,570 --> 00:23:40,580
Want me to be a friend?

374
00:23:41,620 --> 00:23:44,070
They talk to people who are alone.

375
00:23:47,280 --> 00:23:49,590
Thank you for helping me out.

376
00:23:49,590 --> 00:23:53,360
I tend to get shy.

377
00:23:53,360 --> 00:23:56,730
I helped out because it made me nervous.

378
00:23:56,730 --> 00:23:58,750
You were nervous?

379
00:23:58,750 --> 00:24:00,700
In case you'd cry again.

380
00:24:01,970 --> 00:24:05,050
Sounds like you have a low emotional threshold.

381
00:24:05,050 --> 00:24:07,500
What do you mean by threshold?

382
00:24:07,500 --> 00:24:11,930
The lowest level of stimuli needed
to elicit a response.

383
00:24:14,660 --> 00:24:16,190
Fins?

384
00:24:16,190 --> 00:24:18,910
Oh, I free dive.

385
00:24:20,010 --> 00:24:22,350
You must hold your breath well.

386
00:24:26,260 --> 00:24:27,760
The end.

387
00:24:27,760 --> 00:24:29,370
Too short.

388
00:24:29,370 --> 00:24:30,660
Pardon?

389
00:24:30,660 --> 00:24:33,170
Over there, a long banner.

390
00:24:33,170 --> 00:24:34,630
Will you read it for me?

391
00:24:34,630 --> 00:24:37,260
 

392
00:24:40,500 --> 00:24:44,290
You're shy, but you wanted to speak up.

393
00:24:46,160 --> 00:24:48,380
It must be tough for you.

394
00:24:48,380 --> 00:24:50,640
Why do you worry about me?

395
00:24:52,060 --> 00:24:53,770
Are you coming onto me right now?

396
00:24:53,770 --> 00:24:57,160
You almost got picked up earlier.

397
00:24:57,160 --> 00:24:58,920
This isn't about coming onto you.

398
00:24:58,920 --> 00:25:01,000
But you spoke casually and
called me "babe" earlier.

399
00:25:01,000 --> 00:25:03,100
To pretend like I was with you.

400
00:25:07,940 --> 00:25:10,690
But "babe" was a bit too much.

401
00:25:10,690 --> 00:25:12,420
Where are you headed?

402
00:25:12,420 --> 00:25:14,660
I hope it's close.

403
00:25:16,470 --> 00:25:20,050
If I left you in the middle of the street,
you might get picked up again.

404
00:25:29,140 --> 00:25:32,410
Yes, this is my destination.

405
00:25:32,410 --> 00:25:36,560
You know you have map and
ride share apps on your phone.

406
00:25:36,560 --> 00:25:39,450
Why don't you befriend
those guys and find your way?

407
00:25:43,600 --> 00:25:44,880
Don't stare.

408
00:25:44,880 --> 00:25:46,990
You'll bore a hole in my face.

409
00:25:46,990 --> 00:25:48,500
Are you always this friendly?

410
00:25:48,500 --> 00:25:52,400
Watch out for people like me.
Don't just blindly follow.

411
00:25:53,700 --> 00:25:55,230
Move. Don't block the entrance.

412
00:25:55,230 --> 00:25:58,220
You move, Oppa. Don't block the entrance.

413
00:25:59,690 --> 00:26:02,090
She's so strong...

414
00:26:02,090 --> 00:26:03,850
Does she take a herbal tonic?

415
00:26:05,220 --> 00:26:07,670
- What's with you?
- I know, huh?

416
00:26:07,670 --> 00:26:10,560
We were headed to the same place.

417
00:26:16,100 --> 00:26:17,850
What's with him?

418
00:26:20,370 --> 00:26:22,240
"Babe."

419
00:26:22,240 --> 00:26:24,220
"Babe"?

420
00:26:25,140 --> 00:26:26,590
"Babe"...

421
00:26:26,590 --> 00:26:28,630
Why are you looking for your "babe" here?

422
00:26:28,630 --> 00:26:30,460
I wonder why he chose "babe" of all things.

423
00:26:30,460 --> 00:26:31,990
He could've said "friend."

424
00:26:31,990 --> 00:26:34,840
Get a hobby and don't do this here.

425
00:26:34,840 --> 00:26:36,340
I did my hobby.

426
00:26:36,340 --> 00:26:38,280
You want to do it with me? Free diving.

427
00:26:38,280 --> 00:26:39,900
Why do you do that?

428
00:26:39,900 --> 00:26:42,300
But if it was "friend,"

429
00:26:42,300 --> 00:26:45,240
should you be close enough
to grab a drink? Like you and Je Yeon?

430
00:26:45,240 --> 00:26:46,860
I just remembered.

431
00:26:46,860 --> 00:26:50,030
You never listened to others
when you were little, either.

432
00:26:50,030 --> 00:26:51,360
No.

433
00:26:52,430 --> 00:26:54,300
Drinks are a waste of money.

434
00:26:54,300 --> 00:26:56,940
Drinks? My treat. Drink with me.

435
00:26:56,940 --> 00:26:58,570
I don't want to.

436
00:27:01,250 --> 00:27:03,450
I knocked yours over earlier.

437
00:27:04,970 --> 00:27:06,330
Thank you.

438
00:27:06,330 --> 00:27:09,720
Then, I'll ask Sung Je Yeon
to grab a drink with me.

439
00:27:11,730 --> 00:27:13,780
 The customer can't answer the call... 

440
00:27:13,780 --> 00:27:14,830
She didn't pick up.

441
00:27:14,830 --> 00:27:16,730
I texted her and said your place is on fire.

442
00:27:16,730 --> 00:27:18,590
Will she come?

443
00:27:18,590 --> 00:27:21,680
- There's something I haven't told you yet.
 - The customer can't answer... 

444
00:27:21,680 --> 00:27:24,100
I didn't ask you.

445
00:27:24,100 --> 00:27:26,320
Why? I'm curious.

446
00:27:27,890 --> 00:27:30,230
- Hello?
 - What is it? 

447
00:27:30,230 --> 00:27:32,450
I'm holding your actress hostage.

448
00:27:32,450 --> 00:27:34,680
Come here if you want to take her.

449
00:27:34,680 --> 00:27:36,430
Mo Tae Rin, you said there's a fire? Where?

450
00:27:36,430 --> 00:27:38,000
Did you put it out?

451
00:27:39,630 --> 00:27:41,780
Is anyone hurt?

452
00:27:41,780 --> 00:27:43,420
What's with you?

453
00:27:45,460 --> 00:27:47,460
Found it.

454
00:27:49,870 --> 00:27:51,100
You were here, too.

455
00:27:51,100 --> 00:27:53,390
Shouldn't I be? It's my flower shop.

456
00:27:53,390 --> 00:27:55,200
Oh, right.

457
00:27:57,050 --> 00:27:59,910
What's a flower* shop on fire?
("Kkot" means flower in Korean)

458
00:28:04,410 --> 00:28:06,280
Fireworks.
("Bul-kkot" means fireworks)

459
00:28:11,240 --> 00:28:12,740
Fireworks!

460
00:28:12,740 --> 00:28:16,180
I don't believe in hitting women, but...

461
00:28:16,180 --> 00:28:19,050
let me beat you up today. You scared me!

462
00:28:19,050 --> 00:28:21,500
Where would you even hit me?

463
00:28:21,500 --> 00:28:23,880
Gosh, seriously.

464
00:28:23,880 --> 00:28:25,490
Let's beat you up.

465
00:28:25,490 --> 00:28:29,090
- Where would you even hit me?
- Right, you don't even deserve that.

466
00:28:30,580 --> 00:28:32,090
- Hyung.
- What, what, what?

467
00:28:32,090 --> 00:28:34,610
Here. The study guide I put together.

468
00:28:34,610 --> 00:28:36,820
Tell Nu Ri to study it. I'll test her this week.

469
00:28:36,820 --> 00:28:38,500
Okay.

470
00:28:38,500 --> 00:28:40,910
- What are you?
- A tutor.

471
00:28:40,910 --> 00:28:42,900
Who are you teaching, exactly?

472
00:28:42,900 --> 00:28:44,650
My sister.

473
00:28:45,660 --> 00:28:47,820
Oh, really?

474
00:28:48,570 --> 00:28:51,270
Why would you trust him?

475
00:28:57,430 --> 00:28:59,250
Sung Je Yeon.

476
00:28:59,250 --> 00:29:01,700
How come you never talk back to Hyung?

477
00:29:01,700 --> 00:29:03,520
When?

478
00:29:05,370 --> 00:29:06,950
But excuse me...

479
00:29:06,950 --> 00:29:09,850
If you're all done here, can you leave?

480
00:29:09,850 --> 00:29:12,480
Why are you two brothers? For real?

481
00:29:12,480 --> 00:29:14,230
- Yes.
- No.

482
00:29:19,260 --> 00:29:22,040
We'll get going now.

483
00:29:22,040 --> 00:29:23,490
Let's go.

484
00:29:23,490 --> 00:29:26,010
- Go, now?
- We're off. I'm leaving.

485
00:29:26,010 --> 00:29:27,590
Sure, bye.

486
00:29:28,590 --> 00:29:30,310
I'm leaving. See you tomorrow.

487
00:29:30,310 --> 00:29:32,620
Don't come around for a while.

488
00:29:34,800 --> 00:29:36,560
So, we're not.

489
00:29:36,560 --> 00:29:38,010
We weren't.

490
00:29:38,010 --> 00:29:39,610
Until when will we not be?

491
00:29:39,610 --> 00:29:41,020
Who knows?

492
00:29:41,020 --> 00:29:44,660
We might've been brothers if you
had bought that flower basket here.

493
00:29:44,660 --> 00:29:46,770
Gosh, you're still holding onto that.

494
00:29:46,770 --> 00:29:48,870
So adorable.

495
00:29:50,680 --> 00:29:52,560
You're doing pretty well.

496
00:29:52,560 --> 00:29:54,790
Despite that terrible article.

497
00:29:57,150 --> 00:29:59,560
You must have a different attitude,
having hit rock bottom as a kid.

498
00:29:59,560 --> 00:30:04,580
I'm well aware of what it feels
like to hit rock bottom.

499
00:30:06,400 --> 00:30:08,010
I can't even make fun of you.

500
00:30:08,010 --> 00:30:10,110
Aren't you leaving?

501
00:30:10,110 --> 00:30:12,240
I'm going. I'm going.

502
00:30:13,070 --> 00:30:15,530
A stranger, not your brother, is leaving.

503
00:30:19,340 --> 00:30:21,360
Have her study it in advance.

504
00:30:22,800 --> 00:30:25,020
Oh, so quiet...

505
00:30:33,640 --> 00:30:35,900
- You're him, right?
- What?

506
00:30:35,900 --> 00:30:40,370
You and I were the only two
who failed the driving test.

507
00:30:40,370 --> 00:30:45,220
I got so chatty because I was so nervous.

508
00:30:45,220 --> 00:30:46,960
Don't you remember me?

509
00:30:46,960 --> 00:30:49,210
Do I have to remember you
after we failed together?

510
00:30:49,210 --> 00:30:50,849
Here's your car assignment.

511
00:30:50,849 --> 00:30:52,240
 

512
00:30:52,240 --> 00:30:54,640
It was just last week.

513
00:30:56,800 --> 00:31:01,450
I tend to remember only what I want to remember.

514
00:31:01,450 --> 00:31:04,030
It's fateful we met again.

515
00:31:04,030 --> 00:31:06,570
Let's both pass this time.

516
00:31:06,570 --> 00:31:07,900
Don't betray me.

517
00:31:07,900 --> 00:31:10,660
I'm so happy to make a new friend
in Korea after a long time.

518
00:31:10,660 --> 00:31:14,500
You have such a cheery personality.

519
00:31:16,710 --> 00:31:19,840
I'll see you again...

520
00:31:19,840 --> 00:31:21,570
Next time.

521
00:31:22,670 --> 00:31:25,420
I saw him last week.

522
00:31:25,420 --> 00:31:27,650
We failed together.

523
00:31:27,650 --> 00:31:30,280
Oh, the license number...

524
00:31:30,280 --> 00:31:32,850
 

525
00:31:38,290 --> 00:31:40,960
If I process it right away, does it
look like I've been waiting for it?

526
00:31:40,960 --> 00:31:43,390
Because people were talking,

527
00:31:43,390 --> 00:31:45,680
I'm sure you had suspected it.

528
00:31:45,680 --> 00:31:48,110
You were so influential here.

529
00:31:48,110 --> 00:31:50,220
You raised many hoobaes, too.

530
00:31:51,670 --> 00:31:55,890
I didn't speak to other employees.
So, don't worry.

531
00:32:00,000 --> 00:32:02,470
Better wrap up warmly, right?

532
00:32:03,550 --> 00:32:05,590
I'd cheer you...

533
00:32:07,420 --> 00:32:10,250
But not today. Perhaps tomorrow?

