people are all the same...

808
00:51:14,480 --> 00:51:17,710
I agreed to you planting trees,

809
00:51:17,710 --> 00:51:19,260
but I didn't approve of filming.

810
00:51:19,260 --> 00:51:22,670
I see. Please listen to us for a moment...

811
00:51:22,670 --> 00:51:25,250
I haven't heard about any of this.

812
00:51:25,250 --> 00:51:27,360
We're almost done.

813
00:51:27,360 --> 00:51:30,060
Writer, go and help out.

814
00:51:30,060 --> 00:51:32,590
- Hurry up. Go and beg, beg.
 - What are you trying to say? 

815
00:51:32,590 --> 00:51:35,020
 Come on. 

816
00:51:35,020 --> 00:51:37,310
What did he say?

817
00:51:37,310 --> 00:51:40,020
He's quite firm.

818
00:51:40,020 --> 00:51:43,310
He said planting is fine, but no filming at all.

819
00:51:43,310 --> 00:51:46,420
What? Do we need to just leave then?

820
00:51:46,420 --> 00:51:50,080
Let's ditch the planting and pack up.

821
00:51:50,080 --> 00:51:52,860
We'll mess up our schedule
if we miss the boat. That's a wrap!

822
00:51:52,860 --> 00:51:54,990
Let's get moving!

823
00:51:54,990 --> 00:51:56,920
If we're going to throw them out,

824
00:51:56,920 --> 00:52:00,680
can I stay behind and plant them?

825
00:52:00,680 --> 00:52:03,790
They'll grow well as long as they're planted well.

826
00:52:03,790 --> 00:52:05,480
By yourself?

827
00:52:05,480 --> 00:52:08,570
Gosh, how can you plant them alone?
We were going to do it together.

828
00:52:08,570 --> 00:52:10,880
Plus, our lodging ends tonight.

829
00:52:10,880 --> 00:52:13,060
I'll find a place to sleep.

830
00:52:13,060 --> 00:52:14,970
Don't worry about it.

831
00:52:14,970 --> 00:52:17,200
Have a safe trip back.

832
00:52:17,200 --> 00:52:20,790
- Great work.
- Thank you.

833
00:52:20,790 --> 00:52:22,180
- I'm leaving.
- Take care.

834
00:52:22,180 --> 00:52:24,260
Fine then, take care.

835
00:52:24,260 --> 00:52:26,840
Let's get going! Let's move!

836
00:52:26,840 --> 00:52:30,120
 Thank you. 

837
00:52:32,170 --> 00:52:35,620
Sunbae, go ahead. I'll wrap up here.

838
00:52:35,620 --> 00:52:37,150
I trust you.

839
00:52:37,150 --> 00:52:38,640
Thanks.

840
00:52:40,990 --> 00:52:43,620
Gosh, what a shame.

841
00:52:44,620 --> 00:52:47,250
 I gathered all the receipts. 

842
00:52:47,250 --> 00:52:51,030
I'm about to take the boat out. Yes.

843
00:52:51,030 --> 00:52:54,590
I'll see you next time. Okay.

844
00:52:57,170 --> 00:53:00,850
Hello. One ticket for the 4 p.m. boat, please.

845
00:53:00,850 --> 00:53:04,470
Aigoo. The afternoon boats
have all been cancelled.

846
00:53:04,470 --> 00:53:07,700
Boats can't go because of bad weather.

847
00:53:07,700 --> 00:53:11,320
But it's so clear, though.

848
00:53:11,320 --> 00:53:12,790
It is now.

849
00:53:12,790 --> 00:53:15,680
Anyway, get on tomorrow's boat.

850
00:53:30,200 --> 00:53:32,980
It's me. Well...

851
00:53:32,980 --> 00:53:36,420
can I help you?

852
00:53:40,560 --> 00:53:42,560
Isn't it hard by yourself?

853
00:53:42,560 --> 00:53:45,810
Hey, hand it over. I'll carry it.

854
00:53:45,810 --> 00:53:48,550
Save your energy.

855
00:53:48,550 --> 00:53:51,370
We need to start planting early tomorrow morning.

856
00:53:52,920 --> 00:53:57,770
It rains so many times a day.
I guess it's because it's an island.

857
00:53:57,770 --> 00:54:02,120
Right? I can't predict the weather.

858
00:54:05,610 --> 00:54:07,410
 

859
00:54:07,410 --> 00:54:09,640
Oh, right. The blood draw.

860
00:54:09,640 --> 00:54:12,240
Blood draw? Do you have an annual health exam?

861
00:54:12,240 --> 00:54:13,980
My regular exam.

862
00:54:13,980 --> 00:54:15,780
It was scheduled for tomorrow morning,
but I can't make it.

863
00:54:15,780 --> 00:54:16,840
 

864
00:54:18,860 --> 00:54:20,550
Give me that.

865
00:54:20,550 --> 00:54:22,370
I guess we are getting older.

866
00:54:22,370 --> 00:54:24,730
Old and rusty...

867
00:54:24,730 --> 00:54:29,670
Honestly, I was worried about
planting all this by myself.

868
00:54:30,690 --> 00:54:32,530
It worked out.

869
00:54:42,430 --> 00:54:45,090
If they only have one room left here, too,

870
00:54:45,090 --> 00:54:47,470
I'll go sleep at the earlier lodging.

871
00:54:49,900 --> 00:54:52,720
I only have one room left.

872
00:54:52,720 --> 00:54:57,220
We're not in a relationship
where we can share a room.

873
00:54:57,220 --> 00:54:59,900
We need two. Two, please.

874
00:54:59,900 --> 00:55:04,300
I mean it. I bet all the nearby rooms
filled up, too, from all the cancellations.

875
00:55:05,290 --> 00:55:07,070
You sleep here.

876
00:55:07,070 --> 00:55:08,970
We'll take that room.

877
00:55:09,970 --> 00:55:12,240
Yes, hello?

878
00:55:12,240 --> 00:55:15,600
Yes, I was there ten minutes ago-

879
00:55:15,600 --> 00:55:18,970
Oh, yes. You called me
a pretty young lad from Seoul.

880
00:55:18,970 --> 00:55:20,910
Yes, that's me.

881
00:55:22,360 --> 00:55:25,480
You said there's one room left. Yes.

882
00:55:29,270 --> 00:55:32,450
I understand. Thank you.

883
00:55:35,490 --> 00:55:38,360
Good work today. It's late.

884
00:55:38,360 --> 00:55:40,380
Go get some rest.

885
00:55:48,560 --> 00:55:50,370
No, right?

886
00:55:52,070 --> 00:55:55,980
That room didn't get booked, did it?

887
00:56:06,290 --> 00:56:08,650
Do you want to sleep in the car?

888
00:56:10,140 --> 00:56:12,810
For fairness, rock, paper, scissors?

889
00:56:12,810 --> 00:56:14,610
- One round?
- Sure.

890
00:56:14,610 --> 00:56:16,700
Rock, paper, scissors.

891
00:56:16,700 --> 00:56:19,940
Best out of three. Rock, paper, scissors.
Rock, paper, scissors!

892
00:56:20,970 --> 00:56:23,180
I guess I'm sleeping in the car...

893
00:56:23,180 --> 00:56:26,100
I do feel a little bad...

894
00:56:35,790 --> 00:56:39,190
You could sleep in the car.

895
00:56:39,190 --> 00:56:40,810
Why would I?

896
00:56:48,850 --> 00:56:50,550
Great work.

897
00:56:50,550 --> 00:56:53,940
Thanks in advance for your efforts tomorrow.

898
00:56:53,940 --> 00:56:57,580
So professional, when we're sharing a room.

899
00:57:00,300 --> 00:57:02,080
It's just a habit of mine.

900
00:57:02,080 --> 00:57:06,490
Did you finish reading my book?

901
00:57:06,490 --> 00:57:10,740
Sounds like you're curious if I enjoyed it.

902
00:57:10,740 --> 00:57:15,370
Yes. I've been curious ever since
you brought it up yesterday.

903
00:57:17,290 --> 00:57:19,470
It was so hopeful.

904
00:57:19,470 --> 00:57:22,160
Like you wanted to live like that.

905
00:57:22,160 --> 00:57:24,610
I asked if you enjoyed it.

906
00:57:27,060 --> 00:57:30,400
Gosh, I don't want to pay you a compliment,

907
00:57:31,750 --> 00:57:33,990
but it was funny.

908
00:57:33,990 --> 00:57:39,630
And I think I felt a sense of solidarity.

909
00:57:39,630 --> 00:57:42,360
My twenties were kind of like that, too.

910
00:57:43,240 --> 00:57:44,570
What was it like?

911
00:57:44,570 --> 00:57:49,210
Just for taking time off from school,
my entire extended family

912
00:57:49,210 --> 00:57:52,890
pounced at me, scolding and consoling me.

913
00:57:53,630 --> 00:57:56,860
They said I'm experiencing late puberty.

914
00:57:56,860 --> 00:58:00,070
They were more united than
when my family went bankrupt.

915
00:58:00,070 --> 00:58:03,560
You barely slept because you studied
so hard in 12th grade.

916
00:58:03,560 --> 00:58:07,000
Well, I gave up, ultimately.

917
00:58:07,000 --> 00:58:10,290
Turns out I like adventures.

918
00:58:16,870 --> 00:58:19,530
What's weird about this world is that

919
00:58:19,530 --> 00:58:24,060
dirt-cheap, low-budget work
sometimes turns out well,

920
00:58:24,060 --> 00:58:28,170
and huge investments fail sometimes.

921
00:58:28,170 --> 00:58:31,430
You never know what will happen.

922
00:58:31,430 --> 00:58:34,680
So, why do I continue?

923
00:58:38,480 --> 00:58:41,750
Should I give up again and
go on another adventure?

924
00:58:46,890 --> 00:58:49,160
Because of the people?

925
00:58:50,390 --> 00:58:54,050
The times you shared. Stuff like that.

926
00:59:02,160 --> 00:59:04,680
I've never been on a shoot like this.

927
00:59:05,830 --> 00:59:08,350
Where someone is listening to me.

928
00:59:08,350 --> 00:59:12,310
And asking me if I'm okay.

929
00:59:13,800 --> 00:59:16,080
Should we just sleep together?

930
00:59:27,260 --> 00:59:29,950
We'll just hold hands, right?

931
00:59:29,950 --> 00:59:31,510
Sure...

932
00:59:33,440 --> 00:59:35,720
What? No!

933
00:59:36,680 --> 00:59:38,600
No!

934
00:59:38,600 --> 00:59:42,910
There's still just one bed.

935
00:59:42,910 --> 00:59:46,900
Should I sleep in the bed?

936
00:59:46,900 --> 00:59:49,520
Just because you say it softly, it doesn't cut it.

937
00:59:50,500 --> 00:59:54,650
Should we be fair and sleep together?

938
00:59:54,650 --> 00:59:56,000
Huh?

939
01:00:00,300 --> 01:00:03,510
This is the kind of stuff you should say softly.

940
01:00:03,510 --> 01:00:07,450
I'm so tired and sleepy.

941
01:00:07,450 --> 01:00:09,530
Let's kill the lights.

942
01:00:19,180 --> 01:00:21,680
Oh, right.

943
01:00:21,680 --> 01:00:23,990
It's not here...

944
01:00:23,990 --> 01:00:25,900
I am here.

945
01:00:26,900 --> 01:00:29,730
I'm even breathing.

946
01:00:29,730 --> 01:00:32,400
Sounds like you're totally ignoring me.

947
01:00:33,450 --> 01:00:36,590
Right, you're here.

948
01:00:38,630 --> 01:00:41,370
I feel weird...

949
01:00:41,370 --> 01:00:45,110
You're not thinking weird thoughts, are you?

950
01:00:45,110 --> 01:00:47,200
I'm not.

951
01:00:53,830 --> 01:00:55,550
Why not?

952
01:00:56,480 --> 01:00:58,400
You want me to or not?

953
01:00:58,400 --> 01:01:00,190
Whatever.

954
01:01:00,190 --> 01:01:02,080
Forget it. Don't.

955
01:01:08,380 --> 01:01:14,730
You were shining so brightly back then.

956
01:01:14,730 --> 01:01:17,670
 ♫ On a bright day, will our stories be the same? ♫ 

957
01:01:17,670 --> 01:01:19,990
And...

958
01:01:19,990 --> 01:01:24,360
 ♫ I wrote so much, enough
to stay up all night reading ♫ 

959
01:01:24,360 --> 01:01:31,190
 ♫ All the pretty words I couldn't say ♫ 

960
01:01:36,120 --> 01:01:37,880
Goodnight...

961
01:01:38,890 --> 01:01:43,720
 ♫ I visit a day I've recorded in my mind ♫ 

962
01:01:43,720 --> 01:01:46,200
 ♫ You and I are awkward ♫ 

963
01:01:46,200 --> 01:01:51,280
 ♫ Thank goodness we're still there like we were ♫ 

964
01:01:53,090 --> 01:01:59,850
 ♫ I curious about becoming a grown-up,
which seems so real now ♫ 

965
01:01:59,850 --> 01:02:01,770
It's past tense.

966
01:02:06,170 --> 01:02:08,970
I guess not anymore.

967
01:02:12,750 --> 01:02:20,390
 ♫ Walking side by side in lockstep
with you on this street ♫ 

968
01:02:20,390 --> 01:02:25,200
 ♫ I still walk this street every day ♫ 

969
01:02:25,200 --> 01:02:30,000
 ♫ The weary day ♫ 

970
01:02:30,000 --> 01:02:33,810
 ♫ I felt like I was dreaming ♫ 

971
01:02:33,810 --> 01:02:39,780
 ♫ A strange kiss ♫ 

972
01:02:39,780 --> 01:02:44,870
 ♫ It felt like yesterday ♫ 

973
01:02:57,740 --> 01:02:59,260
He's not here.

974
01:03:01,300 --> 01:03:02,930
Must've been a dream.

975
01:03:02,930 --> 01:03:05,240
What a relief.

976
01:03:09,070 --> 01:03:10,770
I'm here.

977
01:03:10,770 --> 01:03:12,810
You want to get rid of me?

978
01:03:14,820 --> 01:03:16,570
What a relief.

979
01:03:16,570 --> 01:03:18,650
It was a dream.

980
01:03:23,980 --> 01:03:31,590
 ♫ If I close my eyes and think of you ♫ 

981
01:03:31,590 --> 01:03:36,030
 ♫ I feel like you'll suddenly appear ♫ 

982
01:03:36,030 --> 01:03:41,100
Gosh, this is why you run a flower shop.

983
01:03:41,100 --> 01:03:46,350
I can smell the earth, and my head is clear.

984
01:03:46,350 --> 01:03:48,400
And the sounds.

985
01:03:48,400 --> 01:03:52,840
I've only heard it on the apps,
but it's great hearing it live.

986
01:03:55,480 --> 01:03:57,000
Oh, right.

987
01:03:57,000 --> 01:04:00,500
What about the cactus? Is it alive?

988
01:04:00,500 --> 01:04:03,720
Why do you keep asking if I killed it?

989
01:04:03,720 --> 01:04:05,640
Because I feel like you'll kill it.

990
01:04:05,640 --> 01:04:08,220
Out of spite toward me.

991
01:04:08,220 --> 01:04:10,030
Should I really kill it?

992
01:04:10,030 --> 01:04:12,380
- Huh?
- Not the cactus.

993
01:04:12,380 --> 01:04:14,820
Want to die?

994
01:04:14,820 --> 01:04:17,200
You brought it from the land?

995
01:04:19,510 --> 01:04:23,400
Why would you bring a car
to an island without any prep?

996
01:04:23,400 --> 01:04:26,340
The PD said she'd cover all car-related costs.

997
01:04:26,340 --> 01:04:28,930
But she must've forgotten and left.

998
01:04:30,940 --> 01:04:33,120
No signal...

999
01:04:34,100 --> 01:04:36,480
Call your insurance.

1000
01:04:36,480 --> 01:04:38,180
Just a second.

1001
01:04:38,180 --> 01:04:42,430
 

1002
01:04:43,120 --> 01:04:45,890
What if the boats get cancelled again?

1003
01:04:45,890 --> 01:04:47,300
And we're trapped on the island again?

1004
01:04:47,300 --> 01:04:49,960
And what if there's only one room again?

1005
01:04:49,960 --> 01:04:52,300
Some TV shows contrive scenes like this.

1006
01:04:52,300 --> 01:04:55,100
Oh, contrived...

1007
01:04:55,100 --> 01:04:58,650
In Tae Rin's current drama, a perfectly
functioning car suddenly breaks down.

1008
01:04:58,650 --> 01:05:01,360
Why? Because it needs to break down.

1009
01:05:01,360 --> 01:05:04,630
What are you looking up right now?

1010
01:05:04,630 --> 01:05:06,430
What?

1011
01:05:06,430 --> 01:05:08,640
Gas station?

1012
01:05:08,640 --> 01:05:10,650
When you run out of gas?

1013
01:05:16,590 --> 01:05:18,060
There we go.

1014
01:05:18,060 --> 01:05:20,010
There's a gas station nearby.

1015
01:05:20,010 --> 01:05:21,810
I'll go get gas.

1016
01:05:23,150 --> 01:05:24,960
Hey.

1017
01:05:24,960 --> 01:05:29,780
I got a text alert earlier about wild boars.

1018
01:05:29,780 --> 01:05:32,730
What if I encounter a wild boar alone?

1019
01:05:32,730 --> 01:05:34,950
That would be more contrived.

1020
01:05:34,950 --> 01:05:38,880
You're not avoiding the insurance,
so you don't increase your premium, right?

1021
01:05:38,880 --> 01:05:40,560
No.

1022
01:05:40,560 --> 01:05:44,030
This is outside of their roadside assistance area.

1023
01:05:44,030 --> 01:05:47,080
Why are you just saying that now?

1024
01:05:47,080 --> 01:05:49,280
Geez.

1025
01:05:51,440 --> 01:05:56,020
Gosh, I'm a rule-follower.

1026
01:05:56,020 --> 01:06:00,510
But the boats are canceled
and the car has broken down.

1027
01:06:00,510 --> 01:06:05,030
Have you always followed the rules?

1028
01:06:07,860 --> 01:06:10,080
I mean...

1029
01:06:10,080 --> 01:06:14,770
I just wonder if you've ever
followed a map you've never seen.

1030
01:06:19,600 --> 01:06:26,000
I've had to go down roads
I wasn't sure were even roads at all.

1031
01:06:26,000 --> 01:06:28,110
Like now?

1032
01:06:28,110 --> 01:06:29,740
Right.

1033
01:06:29,740 --> 01:06:32,150
You said you like adventure.

1034
01:06:34,040 --> 01:06:36,330
- Wow.
- What?

1035
01:06:36,330 --> 01:06:39,270
I've been looking forward to it
since we got here to shoot.

1036
01:06:39,270 --> 01:06:40,970
What?

1037
01:06:40,970 --> 01:06:43,010
Planting trees.

1038
01:06:43,010 --> 01:06:45,050
I wondered when else I'd get a chance.

1039
01:06:45,050 --> 01:06:51,130
It felt like they'd grow up nicely
as long as I plant them well.

1040
01:06:52,700 --> 01:06:59,300
It'll take about five years
before it looks halfway decent.

1041
01:07:00,360 --> 01:07:02,260
It'll be pretty when they bloom.

1042
01:07:02,260 --> 01:07:03,850
What's the meaning behind the flowers?

1043
01:07:03,850 --> 01:07:06,250
I'm not telling you.

1044
01:07:09,900 --> 01:07:13,230
- Sunwoo Hae.
- Yeah?

1045
01:07:13,230 --> 01:07:18,070
So, why did you agree to be on the show?

1046
01:07:24,600 --> 01:07:27,720
You're still curious about that?

1047
01:07:27,720 --> 01:07:32,180
I understand why you kept declining
casting offers this whole time.

1048
01:07:32,180 --> 01:07:38,610
But I don't understand why you accepted this one.

1049
01:07:38,610 --> 01:07:43,570
A heart for my long-lost friend.

1050
01:07:47,590 --> 01:07:51,390
What a sweet sentiment.

1051
01:07:53,700 --> 01:08:00,000
And that's also the meaning
behind the tree we planted.

1052
01:08:01,460 --> 01:08:04,000
What? When did you look it up?

1053
01:08:04,000 --> 01:08:07,200
- When did you have a chance?
- I made it up.

1054
01:08:10,940 --> 01:08:15,290
Gosh, listen to the writer here.

1055
01:08:30,400 --> 01:08:33,740
 ♫ I feel nervous, but I don't know why ♫ 

1056
01:08:33,740 --> 01:08:37,070
 ♫ Faint butterflies in my stomach ♫ 

1057
01:08:37,070 --> 01:08:42,400
 ♫ That familiar voice from the memory ♫ 

1058
01:08:44,850 --> 01:08:49,000
 ♫ Some memories ♫ 

1059
01:08:50,510 --> 01:08:53,080
Careful, you might touch me.

1060
01:08:53,080 --> 01:08:56,300
You might touch me, touch...

1061
01:08:56,300 --> 01:08:58,670
You made contact.

1062
01:08:59,850 --> 01:09:02,030
So hectic.

1063
01:09:02,830 --> 01:09:05,050
Calm down. I won't eat you alive.

1064
01:09:05,050 --> 01:09:10,170
 ♫ We're stuck on that day ♫ 

1065
01:09:12,760 --> 01:09:16,200
 ♫ So beautiful ♫ 

1066
01:09:16,200 --> 01:09:19,360
 ♫ When I look at you blankly ♫ 

1067
01:09:19,360 --> 01:09:21,960
Dodge, if you don't like it.

1068
01:09:21,960 --> 01:09:23,910
What if I don't dislike it?

1069
01:09:25,790 --> 01:09:28,360
Then, I'd be glad.

1070
